From: Claudiu Beznea <claudiu.beznea.uj@bp.renesas.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Nov 2023 10:04:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: ravb: Start TX queues after HW initialization succeeded
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.66
Git-commit: 6f32c086602050fc11157adeafaa1c1eb393f0af

[ Upstream commit 6f32c086602050fc11157adeafaa1c1eb393f0af ]

ravb_phy_start() may fail. If that happens, the TX queues will remain
started. Thus, move the netif_tx_start_all_queues() after PHY is
successfully initialized.

Fixes: c156633f1353 ("Renesas Ethernet AVB driver proper")
Reviewed-by: Sergey Shtylyov <s.shtylyov@omp.ru>
Signed-off-by: Claudiu Beznea <claudiu.beznea.uj@bp.renesas.com>
Reviewed-by: Kalesh AP <kalesh-anakkur.purayil@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/renesas/ravb_main.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/renesas/ravb_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/renesas/ravb_main.c
index 3dab9eae5aaf..6d4c1b9f568b 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/renesas/ravb_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/renesas/ravb_main.c
@@ -1828,13 +1828,13 @@ static int ravb_open(struct net_device *ndev)
 	if (info->gptp)
 		ravb_ptp_init(ndev, priv->pdev);
 
-	netif_tx_start_all_queues(ndev);
-
 	/* PHY control start */
 	error = ravb_phy_start(ndev);
 	if (error)
 		goto out_ptp_stop;
 
+	netif_tx_start_all_queues(ndev);
+
 	return 0;
 
 out_ptp_stop:
